*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*
gluX - cross platform easy OpenGL eXtension Loading
*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*

Linux Install:
--------------

./configure
make
make install

Don't forget to add gluX install path in your CFLAGS 
and gluX library path to your LDFLAGS. Also as gluX
is a shared library, the path to libglux.so should 
be in the LD_LIBRARY_PATH environment variable.

Link with -lglux

Default path are:
  /usr/local/glux
  /usr/local/include
  /usr/local/lib

Windows Install:
----------------

Add the include directory in your preprocessor path and link with
the appropriate version of the library:

lib/win32/vc7.net/glux.lib (single thread)
lib/win32/vc7.net/glux-mt.lib (multi thread)
lib/win32/vc7.net/glux-mt-dll.lib (multi thread dll)

lib/win32/vc8.net/glux-mt.lib (multi thread)
lib/win32/vc8.net/glux-mt-dll.lib (multi thread dll)

If the library directory is empty, compile the solution 'glux-vc2003' or 'glux-vc2005' with
correct code generation settings depending on your version of Visual C++ and the settings
of your project (single thread, multi thread, etc...)

Troubleshooting:
----------------

  see doc/faq.html
